The paper discusses the use of directional antennas and mmWave communications for wireless personal area networks, which falls under the category of networked and internet-connected systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of time allocation for concurrent transmissions, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper focuses on multimedia applications, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also proposes schemes to increase network capacity, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of finding optimum time allocation, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
